description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have significant administrative, telephone and IT experience?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have experience of working within a Health or Social Care environment?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Single Point of Access Administrator role will include taking urgent referrals from GPs, acute hospitals and other Health and Social Care professionals to prevent unnecessary hospital admission and facilitate timely discharge from hospital. The role will also include signposting people/teams to the most appropriate service and passing all referral information to the appropriate Urgent Community Response Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The working hours for this role are 07.00hrs to 20.00hrs across 7 days a week. The roster will be a mixture of early, mid and late shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated member of staff to work as part of the team across 7 days to ensure flexibility and provide cover for each day. If you can demonstrate your flexibility within your working pattern, commitment and willingness to be part of a hardworking and friendly team then this could be the opening for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;There are various hours available on Substantive &amp; Fixed Term (5 months) contracts.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 12/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
